text: Koen Frank Schuiling (1 February 1959) is a Dutch politician. He was born in Rotterdam in 1959 and studied law and administrative sciences at the University of Groningen from 1978 to 1984. After having been parliamentary leader (1996-1998) and alderman (1998-2006), Schuiling served as mayor of Den Helder (2010-2019) and Mayor of Groningen (2019-2024). He retired prematurely as mayor of Groningen; partly due to the asylum issue and gas extraction in Groningen. ==References== Category:1959 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch mayors Category:Dutch politicians Category:People from Rotterdam
